Future Prospects
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
There are potential improvements in a 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

joint
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula $\pod$
\end_inset

+FGD BANFF fit for the T2K experiment.
 As shown in the previous chapter, the number of neutrino-carbon and neutrino-ox
ygen events can be increased by including the 
\begin_inset Formula $\pod$
\end_inset

 data.
 However, since the fits were performed on different T2K run periods, an
 equal POT exposure comparison is useful here.
 Proposing to run a 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

joint
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula $\pod$
\end_inset

+FGD ND constraint using T2K runs 2 - 8, the updated neutrino-nucleus exposures
 are given in 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "tab:Neutrino-exposure-P0DFGD-EqualPOT"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

.
 We see that while the number of neutrino-carbon events is still larger
 in the 
\begin_inset Formula $\pod$
\end_inset

.
 However, the 
\begin_inset Formula $\pod$
\end_inset

 has 25% fewer neutrino-oxygen events in FHC mode and 9% more in RHC mode.
 We can estimate the fractional statistical error (
\begin_inset Formula $\delta N$
\end_inset

) reduction in a joint fit using the data from 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "tab:Neutrino-exposure-P0DFGD-EqualPOT"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 assuming the FGD fit is the nominal ND constraint.
 The fractional errors decrease approximately by
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\begin{aligned}\delta N_{^{12}C}^{\text{FGD1-FHC}} & =\frac{1}{\sqrt{N_{^{12}C}^{\text{FGD1-FHC}}}}\overset{+\pod\text{ Air}}{\longrightarrow}\frac{1}{\sqrt{(1+2.01)N_{^{12}C}^{\text{FGD1-FHC}}}}\sim\frac{1}{\sqrt{3.0}}\\
\delta N_{^{16}O}^{\text{FGD2-FHC}} & =\frac{1}{\sqrt{N_{^{16}O}^{\text{FGD2-FHC}}}}\overset{+\pod\text{ Water}}{\longrightarrow}\frac{1}{\sqrt{(1+0.72)N_{^{12}C}^{\text{FGD1-FHC}}}}\sim\frac{1}{\sqrt{1.7}}\\
\delta N_{^{12}C}^{\text{FGD1-RHC}} & =\frac{1}{\sqrt{N_{^{12}C}^{\text{FGD1-RHC}}}}\overset{+\pod\text{ Air}}{\longrightarrow}\frac{1}{\sqrt{(1+1.60)N_{^{12}C}^{\text{FGD1-RHC}}}}\sim\frac{1}{\sqrt{2.6}}\\
\delta N_{^{16}O}^{\text{FGD2-RHC}} & =\frac{1}{\sqrt{N_{^{16}O}^{\text{FGD2-RHC}}}}\overset{+\pod\text{ Water}}{\longrightarrow}\frac{1}{\sqrt{(1+1.04)N_{^{12}C}^{\text{FGD2-RHC}}}}\sim\frac{1}{\sqrt{2.0}},
\end{aligned}
\]

\end_inset

where combinations of FGD1/2 and FHC/RHC represent the FGD in the different
 beam modes, and an right-point arrow indicates adding the 
\begin_inset Formula $\pod$
\end_inset

 data.
 These results indicate a fractional statistical error reductions around
 
\begin_inset Formula $1/\sqrt{2}$
\end_inset

 for both neutrino-oxygen events and also potentially stronger flux constraint
 from higher statistics.
